<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>DT 466 / DT 570 / HT 570 Service Manual - 2004 Emissions with EGR - EVRT&#174; Electronically Controlled
        Turbocharger - Cleaning - Turbocharger and Related Parts
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc id="svcproc012" graphiccount="0">
        <title>Turbocharger and Related Parts</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use soap and water to clean piping between VGT and air cleaner assembly. Use filtered
                <hotlnk xrefid="safety10" appearance="hottext">compressed air</hotlnk>
                to dry all piping.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use filtered
                <hotlnk xrefid="safety10" appearance="hottext">compressed air</hotlnk>
                to clean the air inlet piping and connecting hoses.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use a suitable solvent and a nylon brush to clean the oil inlet tube and oil drain tube. Use
                filtered
                <hotlnk xrefid="safety10" appearance="hottext">compressed air</hotlnk>
                to dry the tubes. Replace any damaged tubes.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Clean off any remaining gasket material from the turbine housing and exhaust manifold
                mounting surfaces.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
